g.id: Stateful optimality [HLW25] TSr is stateful-optimal if it has the smallest number of states of a reduced state-space for the program
Alg is an excellent POR algorithm if there are polynomials q and r such that Alg builds a POR TSr for P: bounded in size by q(minTS) bounded in time by r(|P|+minTS)
Theorem [HLW25] There is no excellent POR algorithm unless P=NP
